  "issue_number": 4840,
  "issue_title": "v4 - branded primitive types (string, number, ...): unnecessary types inferred, probably with a type perf. impact",
  "issue_body": "The issue is that branded primitive types undergo inference \"workflow\" that scans their entire prototype chain of functions. Probably conditional check branches this way due to intersection of the primitive with the brand which is under the hood an obj structure.\n\n<img width=\"467\" height=\"313\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/a2dc1d2b-bdaf-4749-a324-a070471ef334\" />\n\nI've spotted this issue with `z.treeifyError()`, but it might happen in other context when similar type inference is applied.\n\n[TS Playground Demo](https://www.typescriptlang.org/play/?#code/JYWwDg9gTgLgBAbwF4F84DMoRHAREiAEwHoA3AFlwCgrji4BJAETmAGc4AjKAQwDtCAU0IA6OACFeAuAFcBgqHBgALQXGUQirDvzgROAKzhsYUGQGMYMxQhF2UVADaD4DQnAC8cJCJNRgfADmABQAlCLc-ITBAORuMaFOLnAA8oae3iL6BoKWwQhUcEWshABcjIQANIXFfDwgguU+fgEhiSiJSfBQgmwyjvBeaQa+POiCAAo8UGyC+R1UwOhwwT19AyIKWFChiDVFzvCmgmpePseCSwCeAKJQ26u9-TCb99CJxXB0cADC2GDTNQqIEAdwgSiuYF6+y+9DqDW0cEcmgA1sJZGA4DwOGB-CBgDBgKQ1C0gjDvsB3Owkaj0TJMdi9IZcvAQQTlKwYDisFDYMBepU4IIBK0MXA2SolKo4LiILzCb09MtSYFyfQVNTqZxcjwZLMlVK1JFpNlWHwYApZpZgBA+OL2cZTK0YTBIWoACo9QRuDIAOVtvv6jh4nGcAB5gq6oRBlhdQgBtGKy+X8tgxAC6AD5E5SMy63XBPSdffVTnB-XxA45g6HBBGo4IY0ovQmkzyFAq01nE-DBHmUEA)",
